        "title": "Show HN: Orbit – AR satellite tracker, watch 15k+ objects",
        "link": "https://nagylukas.github.io/orbit.html",
        "description": "<p>Hey HN! I made Orbit, an iOS app that allows you to see the satellites, planets, and constellations above you in AR, on a 2D map, and on a 3D globe.\nThe app includes more than 15,000 objects tracked by CelesTrack, together with their pass predictions, descriptions, and detailed orbital data.\nA searchable catalog of all objects is also available, as well as a built-in chatbot designed to answer any space-related questions you might have.<p>This is my first published iOS app, so any feedback is greatly appreciated!\nApp Store: <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/app/id6772174570\">https://apps.apple.com/app/id6772174570</a></p>\n<hr>\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48873501\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48873501</a></p>\n<p>Points: 9</p>\n<p># Comments: 1</p>",
